      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString()
        Creates a String containing all four fields seperated by new lines. The last line does not have a new line. Could be used to print to a file while creating a songlist.
        Overrides:
        toString in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        Returns a String containing all of the fields, title, music file name, art file name, and the album name. All of the fields are seperated by new lines.

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(java.lang.Object o)
        Compares this SongDetails with the given Object. Non-SongDetails always go after SongDetails, and "exit" always goes before any other song. Sorts first by album name then by song title. Art and music file names do not play a role in comparing.
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable
        Parameters:
        o - An Object to compare this SongDetails with.
        Returns:
        Returns an int less than 0 if this sorts before o, 0 is this equals o, or an int greater than 0 if this sorts after o.
